Howto add the module to a project:

1. install by adding the module to the projects composer file

...
	"require": {
	...
		"symbic/sfw-mvcmodules-sfwdefault": "*",
	...
	}
...

2. register the module with the frontcontroller within the application config

	<frontcontroller>
		<controllerdirectory>
			...
			<sfwdefault><zf:const zf:name="VENDOR_PATH"/>/symbic/sfw-mvcmodules-sfwdefault/modules/sfwdefault/controllers</sfwdefault>
			...
		</controllerdirectory>
		...
		<defaultmodule>sfwdefault</defaultmodule>
		<prefixDefaultModule>true</prefixDefaultModule>
		...
	</frontcontroller>

3. adjust module config

adjust the module config in APPLICATION_PATH/configs/sfwdefault.xml if necessary
see MODULE_DIR/configs/module.default.xml for default settings
see MODULE_DIR/configs/module.template.xml for examples

Please remember to put sfwdefault in the list of public modules whan using a route based ACL list. For the Symbic Acl Module use:

		<systemConfig>
		...
			<acl>
				<active>1</active>
				<requireAuthDefault>1</requireAuthDefault>
				<requireAuthHandler>
					...
				</requireAuthHandler>
				<requireAuthExceptions>
					<default>sfwdefault_*</default>
					...
				</requireAuthExceptions>
			</acl>
		...
		</systemConfig>
